stories.title: England fall agonising seven runs short
stories.summary: After a drubbing at the hands of Sri Lanka in their last match, to say nothing of defeat in the final Ashes Test, Australia got back to winning ways in the latest VB Series encounter with a tense victory over England in Hobart

stories.title: Martyn's last gasp 100 as Australia sets 272
stories.summary: HOBART, Jan 11 AAP - Damien Martyn hit a boundary from the last ball of the innings to set England a target of 272 in the one day international in Hobart today.

stories.title: Australia batting in Hobart
stories.summary: HOBART, Jan 11 AAP - Australian captain Ricky Ponting won the toss and will bat in today's one day cricket international against England at Hobart's Bellerive Oval.
